Apple today released new beta firmware that's designed for the AirPods Pro 2, <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/airpods-pro/">AirPods Pro 3</a>, and <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/airpods/">AirPods 4</a>. The firmware is limited to developers at the current time, and it has a build number of 8B5014c.<br/>
<br/>
<img src="https://images.macrumors.com/article-new/2021/06/AirPods-Pro-Beta-Firmware-2.jpg" alt="" width="2250" height="1266" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-803706" /><br/>
The firmware comes as Apple is testing the iOS 26.1 update. It <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/2025/09/22/ios-26-1-apple-intelligence-languages/">likely adds support</a> for Live Translation in new languages, including Japanese, Korean, Italian, and Chinese (both Mandarin Traditional and Simplified).<br/>
<br/>
With <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/ios-26/">iOS 26</a>, <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/ipados-26/">iPadOS 26</a>, and macOS Tahoe, Apple added a beta firmware update installation option that's available from the AirPods settings interface when the AirPods are connected to an <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/guide/iphone/">iPhone</a>, <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/ipad/">iPad</a>, or Mac, which facilitates beta testing.<br/>
<br/>
Developers can use the beta option to turn on beta downloads.<br/>This article, &quot;<a href="https://www.macrumors.com/2025/10/09/apple-airpods-beta-firmware-8b5014c/">Apple Releases New Beta Firmware for AirPods Pro 2, AirPods Pro 3 and AirPods 4</a>&quot; first appeared on <a href="https://www.macrumors.com">MacRumors.com</a><br/><br/><a href="https://forums.macrumors.com/threads/apple-releases-new-beta-firmware-for-airpods-pro-2-airpods-pro-3-and-airpods-4.2468799/">Discuss this article</a> in our forums<br/><br/>